    "body": "Hey guys, I was thinking that could be a good ideia create a decorator to put in the head of method, to show what kind of content-type that rest service will return. \n\nSomething like that:\n\n``` python\n\n@return_json\n@app.route('/user/email')\ndef get_user_email():\n   return {'email': 'example@email.com'}\n```\n\nSo, in the return_json decorator we could change the content-type of response. If someone think that is a good ideia, I can implement and send a pull request.\n",
