            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "That's extremely easy to implement in your own application. No need for it to be in Flask itself.\n\nBesides that, if you return JSON using the `jsonify` function it'll already set the proper content-type header.\n\nOh, and the route decorator always needs to be the topmost one. Otherwise it'll receive the undecorated function. Your example does this:\n\n```\nget_user_email = return_json(app.route('/user/email')(get_user_email))\n```\n"
